In 2000,<ref name="GR2" /> there were 834 people, 298 households, and 230 families residing in the town; in 2010, its population was 912.<ref name="Census 2010">{{cite web |title=Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics: 2010 Census Summary File 1 (DP-1), Dasher town, Georgia |url=https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_SF1/SF1DP1/1600000US1321744 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://archive.today/20200213120817/https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_SF1/SF1DP1/1600000US1321744 |archive-date=February 13, 2020 |accessdate=December 18, 2019 |website=American FactFinder |publisher=U.S. Census Bureau}}</ref> By the 2020 census, its population was 890.

